      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but there was no man — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Namely, in Saul’s court or camp: none of my former relations, friends or acquaintance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that would know me — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Own me, or show any respect or kindness to me. The verb, in the first clause of the verse, being in the imperative; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "look on my right hand,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c. — Dr. Horne considers the words as a request to God to look on his destitute condition, and to pity and relieve him; but Bishop Patrick views them as a kind of soliloquy, and explains them thus, “Look about thee, O my soul, and see if thou canst spy any hope of relief from thy best and most powerful friends: there are none of them that dare own thee; nor do I know whither to flee for safety.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Refuge failed, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "faileth me — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "There is no patron on earth to whom I can commit my cause, nor any help in man for me. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "No man cared, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "rather ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "careth, for my soul ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Or, for my life, namely, to preserve it: but they all conspire to take it away.",
        "children": []
